{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsU7Pihi3WLkTHcfadsr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The full-restart upgrade to 8.11.1 is complete and verified:\n\n1. **Version**: all 3 nodes report `8.11.1` (`es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2`).\n2. **Cluster reachable, 3 nodes**: `_cluster/health` shows `status: green`, `number_of_nodes: 3`, all shards active.\n3. **Data intact**: `app-data` index still has all 3 seeded docs (`seed-1`, `seed-2`, `seed-3`).\n\nWhat I did:\n- Flushed the index, then fully scaled the StatefulSet to 0 replicas (true full stop, not a rolling restart) and waited for termination.\n- Patched all 4 container images (3 init containers + main) to `8.11.1` via `kubectl set image`.\n- Scaled back to 3 replicas and waited for all pods Ready.\n- Per the note, checked `/_cluster/settings` post-restart and found `cluster.routing.allocation.enable` had been set (by an external process) to `\"none\"`, which was blocking replica shard allocation (cluster stuck yellow). Reset it to `\"all\"`, after which the cluster went green with all shards allocated."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":921,"cache_read_input_tokens":90632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":921},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a34340d1-dcae-4c45-9625-2e89b82d9d75","uuid":"f60816d3-e871-4897-9827-c7ec94f92a6b","request_id":"req_011CcsU7NfwpmsyyL1W9heyC"}
